
Overview of verb repudiate

The verb repudiate has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (3) disown, renounce, repudiate -- (cast off; "She renounced her husband"; "The parents repudiated their son")
2. (1) repudiate -- (refuse to acknowledge, ratify, or recognize as valid; "The woman repudiated the divorce settlement")
3. repudiate -- (refuse to recognize or pay; "repudiate a debt")
4. repudiate -- (reject as untrue, unfounded, or unjust; "She repudiated the accusations")
